result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (7th) and Operating w/ PAC (7th, 8th or 9th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (7th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (7th, 8th or 9th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Daniel N. Bobbe was found guilty of OWI (7th), a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 9:31 am - DA calls case and states appearances.  Defendant Daniel N. Bobbe appeared with attorney Christina M Writz.  Mark T. Fuhr appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  This is outside the presence of jury.  Discussion of motion filed by DE.  Motion is denied.  Discussion of jury instruction.  Atty Writz withdraws request.  Parties stipulate the OAR charge will be dealt with by a trial to court.  Motion in limine regarding charge is granted. Sequestration granted except for alcohol expert.  Parties stipulate that there be no mention of penalties or prior conviction.   9:45 am - In the presence of jurors.  Jury selection.  Jurors called and sworn.  DA introduces case to jurors.  Voir Dire.  Parties exercise strikes.  Jurors sworn.  Exhibits 1-30 marked.  Sidebar.  Opening arguments.  Jurors excused at 10:35 am.  Discussion regarding earlier sidebar.  Off record at 10:36 am.  Back on record at 10:52 am.  Out of presence of jury.  10:55 am  Back in presence of jury.  Brittany Van Galder called and sworn.  Direct by DA.  Cross by Atty Writz. Redirect by DA.  Alan Borger called and sworn.  Direct by DA.  Cross by Atty Writz.  Out of presence of jury/off record at 11:10 am.  Back in presence of jury at 11:14 am.  Mark Krueger called and sworn.  Direct by DA.  Cross by Atty Writz.  Deputy Joseph Janak called and sworn.  Direct by DA.  Exhibits 1-28 identified, offered and received.  Continued direct.  Traffic stop video shown.  Continued direct.  Exhibit 29 identified, offered and received.  Continued direct.  Exhibit 30 identified, offered and received.  Continued direct.  Cross by Atty Writz.  12:24 pm.  Jury is excused.  Off record at 12:24 pm.  Court rules on expert witness.  12:26 pm Back on record.  State rests.  1:14 pm - Back on record and in the presence of jurors.  Atty Writz calls DE Daniel Bobbe.  Sworn.  Direct by Atty Writz.  Exhibit 31 marked and identified.  Exhibit 32 marked and identified.  Exhibits 31 and 32 offered and received.  Cross by DA.  Exhibit 33 marked and identified.  Re-direct by Atty Writz.  Re-cross by DA.  Timothy Christianson called and sworn.  Direct by Atty Writz.  Cross by DA.  Re-direct by Atty Writz.  Mary Catherine McMurray called and sworn.  Direct by Atty Writz.  Exhibit 34 marked, identified, offered and received.  Cross by DA.  Defense rests.  DA moves Exhibit 33 into evidence, offered and received.  Jury is excused at 2:21 pm.  Court and counsel discuss jury instructions.  Adj. 2:29pm.   Court resumes at 2:35pm, outside presence of jury.  Court and counsel continue with jury instruction conference. Atty. Writz states motion for dismissal.  DA states objection to motion.  Court denies motion.  Jury in courtroom at 2:38pm.  Closing argument by DA.  Closing argument by Atty. Writz.  Rebuttal by DA.  Court reads Jury Instructions.  Bailiff is sworn.  Jury is excused to deliberate 3:14pm  Court adjourn 3:14pm.  3:20pm off the record, jury requests all exhibits.  Court directs Clerk to give all exhibits to bailiff for the jury.  Jury returns with verdict 4:26pm.  Verdict is published by the Court.  Defendant is found guilty of Count 1 and Count 2.  Atty. Writz requests jury be polled. Jury polled - unaminous.  Jury is excused at 4:27pm.  On motion of DA, Court enters judgment of guilty to both counts.  DA moves to dismiss Count 3 (OAR), Court so orders.  DA moves to dismiss 14TR1019 and 14TR1020, Court so grants on general assignment.  DA requests the defendant be remanded into custody.  Atty. Writz is not recommending a PSI.  Court will proceed to sentencing.  DA states recommendation.  Atty. Writz comments.  Court imposes:   Count 1 - Prison 5 years, with earn release program and substance abuse program (3 years initial confinement/2 years extended supervision)  $2,452.00 fine (inclusive of DNA surcharge), $65.50 State Blood Test, $71.20 Witness Fees-maybe amended within 14 days, DL revoked 3 years, AODA, IID 3 years.  Written explanation of determinate sentence is completed, copy given to defendant.  Appeal rights given.  Court adjourned 4:46pm.
